~$33/mo single
~$98/mo per-AZ" style="rounded=1;arcSize=6;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#E8F5E9;strokeColor=#558B2F;fontColor=#232F3E;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;strokeWidth=1.6;dashed=0;verticalAlign=middle;align=center;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="470" y="440" width="220" height="86" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="igw2" value="Internet
Gateway" style="rounded=1;arcSize=6;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#F3E5F5;strokeColor=#8C4FFF;fontColor=#232F3E;fontSize=10;fontStyle=1;strokeWidth=1.6;dashed=0;verticalAlign=middle;align=center;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="780" y="450" width="120" height="66" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="net2" value="Public internet
Twilio, SMTP, carriers
(no VPC endpoint)" style="rounded=1;arcSize=6;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFEBEE;strokeColor=#C62828;fontColor=#232F3E;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;strokeWidth=1.6;dashed=0;verticalAlign=middle;align=center;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="980" y="440" width="270" height="86" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="cn" value="none

zero NAT, the private 0.0.0.0/0
routes vanish. pods still reach
S3 + ECR via endpoints, but SMTP
and carriers are unreachable.
cheapest, cannot do the job." style="rounded=1;arcSize=6;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#F5F5F5;strokeColor=#90A4AE;fontColor=#37474F;fontSize=10;fontStyle=0;strokeWidth=1.6;dashed=0;verticalAlign=middle;align=center;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="80" y="620" width="420" height="150" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="cs" value="single   (dev default)

one NAT in one AZ (~$33/mo).
other AZs route cross-AZ to it.
not HA: lose that AZ, lose egress.
fine for dev, name the risk for prod." style="rounded=1;arcSize=6;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#E8F5E9;strokeColor=#558B2F;fontColor=#33691E;fontSize=10;fontStyle=0;strokeWidth=1.6;dashed=0;verticalAlign=middle;align=center;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="520" y="620" width="420" height="150" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="cp2" value="per_az   (prod)

one NAT per AZ (~$98/mo).
each AZ egresses locally.
survives an AZ outage.
that is the +$65/mo HA line item." style="rounded=1;arcSize=6;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#E3F2FD;strokeColor=#1976D2;fontColor=#0D47A1;fontSize=10;fontStyle=0;strokeWidth=1.6;dashed=0;verticalAlign=middle;align=center;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="960" y="620" width="420" height="150" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="EP3p2_e0" value="AWS APIs" style="edgeStyle=none;rounded=0;html=1;endArrow=block;strokeColor=#6A1B9A;strokeWidth=2;dashed=0;exitX=1;exitY=0.35;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=0;entryY=0.5;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;fontSize=10;fontColor=#37474F;labelBackgroundColor=#ffffff;" edge="1" parent="1" source="pod" target="epg"><mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry"></mxGeometry></mxCell><mxCell id="EP3p2_e1" value="private" style="edgeStyle=none;rounded=0;html=1;endArrow=block;strokeColor=#6A1B9A;strokeWidth=2;dashed=1;exitX=1;exitY=0.5;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=0;entryY=0.5;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;fontSize=10;fontColor=#37474F;labelBackgroundColor=#ffffff;" edge="1" parent="1" source="epg" target="apis"><mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry"></mxGeometry></mxCell><mxCell id="EP3p2_e2" value="third-party egress" style="edgeStyle=none;rounded=0;html=1;endArrow=block;strokeColor=#C62828;strokeWidth=2;dashed=0;exitX=1;exitY=0.8;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=0;entryY=0.5;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;fontSize=10;fontColor=#37474F;labelBackgroundColor=#ffffff;" edge="1" parent="1" source="pod" target="nat"><mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry"></mxGeometry></mxCell><mxCell id="EP3p2_e3" value="" style="edgeStyle=none;rounded=0;html=1;endArrow=block;strokeColor=#C62828;strokeWidth=2;dashed=0;exitX=1;exitY=0.5;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=0;entryY=0.5;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;fontSize=10;fontColor=#37474F;labelBackgroundColor=#ffffff;" edge="1" parent="1" source="nat" target="igw2"><mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry"></mxGeometry></mxCell><mxCell id="EP3p2_e4" value="" style="edgeStyle=none;rounded=0;html=1;endArrow=block;strokeColor=#C62828;strokeWidth=2;dashed=0;exitX=1;exitY=0.5;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=0;entryY=0.5;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;fontSize=10;fontColor=#37474F;labelBackgroundColor=#ffffff;" edge="1" parent="1" source="igw2" target="net2"><mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry"></mxGeometry></mxCell></root></mxGraphModel></diagram><diagram name="EP3 - Security group layers" id="EP3p3"><mxGraphModel dx="1400" dy="900" grid="0" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="1450" pageHeight="650" math="0" shadow="0"><root><mxCell id="0"/><mxCell id="1" parent="0"/><mxCell id="t1" value="EP3: security groups" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;fontColor=#232F3E;fontSize=20;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="21" width="900" height="28" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="t2" value="Four layers, kept separate. A security group is a stateful allow-only firewall on an ENI." style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;fontColor=#5A6B7B;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="50" width="900" height="28" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="Cluster" value="Cluster SG

EKS creates it.
Control plane and nodes
talk over it.
You mostly leave it alone." style="rounded=1;arcSize=6;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FDECEA;strokeColor=#DD3522;fontColor=#9b2418;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;strokeWidth=1.6;dashed=0;verticalAlign=top;spacingTop=6;align=center;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="70" y="160" width="320" height="190" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="Node" value="Node SG

On the EC2 instances.
Host-level allow rules,
e.g. NLB health checks
come in here." style="rounded=1;arcSize=6;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FDECEA;strokeColor=#DD3522;fontColor=#9b2418;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;strokeWidth=1.6;dashed=0;verticalAlign=top;spacingTop=6;align=center;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="420" y="160" width="320" height="190" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="Pod" value="Pod SG (opt-in)

SecurityGroupPolicy via
the VPC CNI. A real SG
on one pod, not the node.
For pod-level isolation." style="rounded=1;arcSize=6;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FDECEA;strokeColor=#DD3522;fontColor=#9b2418;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;strokeWidth=1.6;dashed=0;verticalAlign=top;spacingTop=6;align=center;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="770" y="160" width="320" height="190" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="Endpoints" value="Endpoints SG

Allows 443 in from the
VPC CIDR only, so pods
reach the interface
endpoints. Nothing else." style="rounded=1;arcSize=6;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#E8F5E9;strokeColor=#2E7D32;fontColor=#1b5e20;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;strokeWidth=1.6;dashed=0;verticalAlign=top;spacingTop=6;align=center;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="1120" y="160" width="320" height="190" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="rot" value="Rule of thumb:  cluster SG = control-plane chatter (leave it).   node SG = host rules like NLB health checks.   pod SG = surgical per-pod isolation, only when it matters.   endpoints SG = 443 from the VPC CIDR, nothing more." style="rounded=1;arcSize=6;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFF8E1;strokeColor=#FBC02D;fontColor=#5F4B00;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;strokeWidth=1.6;dashed=0;verticalAlign=middle;align=center;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="70" y="400" width="1300" height="80" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="state" value="Stateful: the SG remembers an outbound connection and auto-allows the reply, so you never write a matching inbound rule for every response." style="rounded=1;arcSize=6;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#E8EAF6;strokeColor=#3F51B5;fontColor=#283593;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;strokeWidth=1.6;dashed=0;verticalAlign=middle;align=center;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="70" y="520" width="900" height="70" as="geometry"/></mxCell></root></mxGraphModel></diagram></mxfile>